==English==

===Noun===
'''[[A]] [[cup]]'''
# A standard, relatively small, [[bra]] [[cup size]], consisting of a measurement around the [[bust]] that is one [[inch]] longer than a measurement around the band, plus five inches.
# ''(by [[synecdoche]])'' A woman whose breasts fit a A-cup bra.

===Quotations===
* '''1999,''' Elizabeth M. Hoekstra, M. Beth Cutaiar, ''Just for Girls'' [http://books.google.com/books?ie=UTF-8&hl=en&id=W6VI7o3romMC&pg=PA68&lpg=PA68&sig=AWBt6VJifI_c66JiwCTXyJIO2C0]
*: The smallest cup size is AAA. The largest is a DD/E.  An '''A cup''' is fairly small, just a little swell of breast tissue.
* '''2003,''' Michelle Copeland ''Change Your Looks, Change Your Life'' ISBN 0060518979 
*:''"Gabrielle had alwats been an '''A cup''', but her pregnancy had left her breasts flat as pancakes, and she wanted to go to a C cup and eliminate some of the sag."''  
* '''2004,''' Z Paul Lorenc, Trish Hall, ''A Little Work'' [http://books.google.com/books?ie=UTF-8&hl=en&id=gSO-sq1C6ecC&pg=PA11&lpg=PA11&sig=xBeJ_aJP71I9cVQV3ZZOR0e1Y4A]
*: Directly after Julia is Patricia, who, oddly enough, is another young blond mother from the suburbs. She, too, is an '''A cup''' wanting breast implants.

